    "narrative": "For April 22, 2026, the optimizer highlights **James Wood** (78.42) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) as our high-ceiling anchors. **James Wood** draws a favorable matchup against a weak 5.07 xERA arm, and his lead-off spot maximizes his stolen base potential, which remains our primary objective. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive park factor boost and the combination of a high-xERA opponent and a slow-delivering pitcher, which increases the likelihood of a multi-bagger day. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (71.51) also earns a strong start; his matchup against Bassitt is bolstered significantly by favorable wind conditions at the stadium, turning an already solid base projection into a high-efficiency play.\n\nOur middle-infield rotation sees **Brice Turang** (61.93) take the priority slot over **Trevor Story** (52.19) and **Alex Freeland** (50.23). While **Brice Turang** faces a respectable arm, his role at the top of the order provides the necessary floor to suppress the variance of our lower-scoring bench pieces. The most difficult decision rested on **Kyle Karros**, who posted a 62.71 score but ultimately landed on the bench due to the sheer density of superior options in our outfield and utility slots. **Kyle Karros** has shown efficiency, but the specific combination of **Mickey Moniak**\u2019s speed-advantage matchup and the raw power output expected from **Austin Riley** (67.02) and **Josh Naylor** (67.20) created a barrier to entry he couldn't clear today.\n\nRisks remain, particularly regarding our catching tandem. Both **Dalton Rushing** (57.03) and **Luis Campusano** (59.72) are projected with pending lineups, and their scores are sensitive to order fluctuations; should either drop lower in the order, their efficiency will plummet. Additionally, **Corbin Carroll** (53.84) faces a stiff challenge against a 2.60 xERA pitcher, significantly dragging down his base projection. Despite the scarcity of stolen bases, we are proceeding with caution here, as the quality of the opposing arm outweighs the potential for a favorable platoon or order placement.",
